{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01CCfNh19Aw7gizvgAKGzntD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nUS-028 is complete. Here's what was implemented:\n\n**Kernel change** (`integrate.cu`):\n- Added `ACCEL_MAX = 5000.0f` and `ACCEL_MAX_SQ` constants\n- After computing `accel = sph_force/mass + gravity + buoyancy`, added a 5-line block that clamps `|accel|` to 5000 using the same squared-magnitude-then-sqrt pattern as the existing velocity clamp\n- Silent clamping — no error, just direction-preserving magnitude limit\n\n**Tests** (`test_integrate.py`):\n- `test_accel_clamp_overlapping_particles` — 10 particles at same position with 1e8 force, 100 steps: all stay bounded, no NaN\n- `test_accel_clamp_normal_unaffected` — moderate SPH force (accel ~631) not altered by clamp\n- `test_accel_clamp_exact_threshold` — force producing accel=10000 gets clamped to exactly 5000\n- Updated `test_velocity_clamp` to use moderate force + high initial velocity (since the old 1e6 force now gets accel-clamped first)\n\nAll 32 tests pass.\n\n<promise>COMPLETE</promise>"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":230,"cache_read_input_tokens":82580,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":230},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a5d0dd0a-9cf9-442a-8f94-f9b3ba264427","uuid":"dafe7a3c-28c5-4b05-8fe1-7abb6fa1aab7"}
